summary: I think weve all been fucked over so many times before that people are worrying about killing eve like respect the journey!!!...
question: I think weve all been fucked over so many times before that people are worrying about killing eve like respect the journey!!! Were gonna get so much more sexy content!!!
answer: i.. understand that people have been fucked over by too many cw shows gaybait in the past but like it annoys me how easily people are willing to turn on a show thats written by women with a woc as a lead bc they didnt get exactly the unrealistic season final they imagined. eve+villanelle not fucking right there in the ancient ruins of rome isnt gaybaiting. those characters are CANONICALLY attracted to each other, and into women. its not subtext. v literally told eve she loves her, there were so many amazing moments in the episode and it made perfect sense what happened…eve just killed someone to protect v ad is emotionally crumbling, of course she wouldnt run away to alaska. she needs to work through what shes done, its a huge moment for her character arc. only when eve has accepted what shes done, what kind of person shes become - or always was, shell be able to let herself be with V physically. i love the slow burn i love the angst and the writing is amazing, they know exactly who their characters are. also i saw some posts from people saying what will happen now that v will get over eve? like where is that eve coming from? the entire show is about their relationship. its a will they/wont they but with murder. they wont stop chasing each other. i cant wait for what theyll come up for s3 and how eve will react with everything that happened, what happens with niko and everything else!!

summary: I was thinking just this morning about how amazing Jodie is. Generally speaking, I would write “Scottish accent,” for example,...
text: I was thinking just this morning about how amazing Jodie is. Generally speaking, I would write “Scottish accent,” for example, and then Jodie would just come in and do it perfectly. She’s an extraordinary mimic, with an unbelievable ear. She literally just learned French, she does it all by ear. She likes to keep Villanelle very far away from her own accent, which I think is wise, but there hasn’t been an accent she hasn’t been able to do, or a language.
